<div class="col five-sm clear">
<h2 id="section-top">Overview</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="news-teaser">
<div class="panel panel-nonedit module">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p><a href="#news-title">News:</a></p>
<ul><li>Clinic Locations</li></ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentf736209e3c4a4d64b05a95d4eee30d80">
</div>
<p>Mayflower Healthcare Alliance are an NHS Healthcare Provider offering a comprehensive range of Dermatology, Urology, Gynaecology and Neurology services for patients in the Basildon, Brentwood, Billericay, Wickford and Thurrock areas.</p>
<p>Our specialist team includes consultants, General Practitioners with Extended Responsibilities (GPwER), Associate Specialists, Surgeons and Specialist Nurses.</p>
<p>Our clinics operate on weekdays, weekends and evenings are a conveniently located with the community in Billericay, Brentwood and Thurrock Essex, within easy reach of the A12, A127, A13 and the M25.</p>
<p>For more information please contact our patient information centre on 01277 657835.<br/><br/></p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="news-panel box">
<h3 id="news-title">Latest news</h3>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="panel article-item">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h4 id="Article-207994">Clinic Locations</h4>
<div id="imageContent418f7ec841c4448595a69ce04f4eddac">
</div>
<p><strong>Brentwood Community Hospital</strong> - we undertake our minor ops here as well as providing consultation appointments.  The car park at Brentwood Community Hospital is free.</p>
<p><strong>Billericay Health Centre</strong> - this venue houses different services, including a GP Practice.  There is a free car park.</p>
<p><strong>East Thurrock Medical Centre</strong> - this venue is an independent GP Practice.  Access to our clinics are via the back entrance where there is a small cark park that is used by the Practice Staff and patients.  There are some roads around the Medical Centre where patients can park</p>
<p><strong>Thurrock Health Centre</strong> - this venue is an independant GP Practice and access is via the front door and Thurrock Health Centre Staff will direct our patients to a waiting area.  There are no car parking facilities at Thurrock Health Centre, which is on the High Street but there is a multi story car park attached to the shopping centre and patients can also park at Morrisons supermarket where there is a charge and a maximum stay of 3 hours</p>
<p>Please don't hesitate to contact our patient information line if you require any further information on our clinic localities.</p>
<p class="last-updated">Last updated on 12 November 2018.</p>
